  "title": "Game Designer/ Senior Game Designer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Lead the conceptualization, design, and iteration of game mechanics, systems, and levels for incubation projects.</p></li><li><p>Develop compelling gameplay loops, player progression models, and core interaction patterns.</p></li><li><p>Create design documentation (GDDs, feature specs, wireframes) to communicate design intent.</p></li><li><p>Collaborate closely with developers to implement and refine gameplay features.</p></li><li><p>Run and evaluate playtests to gather user feedback and continuously improve prototypes.</p></li><li><p>Maintain a backlog of viable game concepts and contribute to ideation pipelines.</p></li><li><p>Support game pitches and internal evaluations by presenting design thinking and rationale.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p><ul><li>Bachelor's degree or above in Game Design, Computer Science, or a related field.</li></ul></p><p><ul><li>Minimum 3 years of relevant experience (including internship) in game design, preferably with shipped titles or prototypes.</li></ul></p><p><ul><li>Strong portfolio showcasing design systems, levels, or full game experiences.</li></ul></p><p><ul><li>Proficiency with game engines (e.g. Unity, Unreal Engine) and design tools (e.g. level editors, visual scripting).</li></ul></p><p><ul><li>Solid grasp of user experience, player psychology, and retention mechanics.</li></ul></p><p><ul><li>Comfortable iterating quickly and integrating feedback into design cycles.</li></ul></p><ul><li>Strong communication and documentation skills for design handoff and collaboration.</li></ul><p></p>",
